HEADWORD: White elephant
<hw>White elephant</hw>. <def>Something requiring much care and expense
to maintain and yielding little profit, and often difficult to sell; any
burdensome possession.</def> <mark>[Slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

